==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corolla
<hw>Co*rol"la</hw> <pr>(k?-r?l"l?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>corolla</ets> a little crown or garland, dim. of <ets>corona</ets>.
See <er>Crown</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The inner envelope of
a flower; the part which surrounds the organs of fructification,
consisting of one or more leaves, called <xex>petals</xex>. It is
usually distinguished from the calyx by the fineness of its texture and
the gayness of its colors. See the Note under
<er>Blossom</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corollaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
